rComments: She is a decent professor however her grading criteria for assignments are unclear and TAs are horrible markers.

She's new, and she clearly cares. Is fairly lenient with extensions and projects aren't impossible. However, she's clearly a new prof. Has trouble making engaging lectures and I often walk away not really knowing what I learned. Feels like she'll be very solid in 2-3 years, but for now a bit shaky. Still, if you have her, not the end of the world.

I'll keep it simple: extremely disorganized; sounds unconfident/confused during her own lectures; extremely heavy readings that are rarely ever discussed during class; mandatory discussion groups after EVERY class to "prove you did the readings"; and an oddly hard marker. I do NOT recommend taking her courses.
